title: Medieval warrior queen
itunes:title: Medieval warrior queen
itunes:subtitle: Catherine Hanley tells the story of Empress Matilda, whose battle for the English throne became known as ‘the anarchy’.
description:
Historian Catherine Hanley tells the story of Empress Matilda, the daughter of Henry I whose battle with Stephen for the English throne in the 12th century became known as ‘the anarchy’.

Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information.
